# Payments Domain – User Stories

# Purpose

This document defines user stories for the Payments Domain in a structured format that connects business needs to domain concepts, rules, and acceptance criteria.

Each story ensures traceability from user value → domain behavior → business rules.

---

# User Stories

---

## US-001: Create a Payment

| Field          | Content                                               |
| -------------- | ----------------------------------------------------- |
| User Story ID  | US-001                                                |
| Role           | Orders System / Billing System                        |
| Capability     | Initiate a payment request                            |
| Value          | Ensure clients can pay for services or goods reliably |
| Domain Concept | Payment, PaymentIntent                                |
| Business Rules | RULE-001, RULE-002, RULE-005                          |

### Acceptance Criteria

* A payment can be created with a valid amount and currency.
* A unique payment ID is generated.
* Duplicate requests with the same idempotency key do not create multiple payments.
* Payment is initially stored in “Initiated” state.
* Payment creation emits a PaymentCreated event.

---

## US-002: Process a Payment

| Field          | Content                                                |
| -------------- | ------------------------------------------------------ |
| User Story ID  | US-002                                                 |
| Role           | Payments Domain (System)                               |
| Capability     | Execute payment through external provider              |
| Value          | Ensure payments are successfully processed and settled |
| Domain Concept | PaymentTransaction, PaymentProvider                    |
| Business Rules | RULE-006, RULE-011, RULE-012                           |

### Acceptance Criteria

* Payment is sent to a valid payment provider.
* Only one provider is used per transaction attempt.
* Provider response is recorded in a PaymentTransaction.
* Payment status is updated based on provider response.
* PaymentCompleted or PaymentFailed event is emitted accordingly.

---

## US-003: Handle Payment Failure

| Field          | Content                                      |
| -------------- | -------------------------------------------- |
| User Story ID  | US-003                                       |
| Role           | Payment Provider / Payments System           |
| Capability     | Record and manage failed payments            |
| Value          | Ensure failures are traceable and actionable |
| Domain Concept | Payment, PaymentStatus                       |
| Business Rules | RULE-010, RULE-015                           |

### Acceptance Criteria

* Failed payment attempts are recorded with a failure reason.
* Payment status is set to Failed.
* PaymentFailed event is emitted.
* Failure is visible for support and reconciliation.

---

## US-004: Refund a Payment

| Field          | Content                                                  |
| -------------- | -------------------------------------------------------- |
| User Story ID  | US-004                                                   |
| Role           | Customer Support / Finance Team                          |
| Capability     | Reverse a completed payment                              |
| Value          | Allow correction of payments and customer reimbursements |
| Domain Concept | Refund, Payment                                          |
| Business Rules | RULE-008, RULE-009                                       |

### Acceptance Criteria

* Refund can only be created for completed payments.
* Refund amount cannot exceed original payment amount.
* Partial refunds are supported.
* Refund status is tracked independently.
* PaymentRefunded event is emitted.

---

## US-005: Query Payment Status

| Field          | Content                                   |
| -------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| User Story ID  | US-005                                    |
| Role           | Customer Support / Orders System          |
| Capability     | Retrieve payment status                   |
| Value          | Provide visibility into payment lifecycle |
| Domain Concept | Payment                                   |
| Business Rules | RULE-013                                  |

### Acceptance Criteria

* Payment status can be retrieved by payment ID.
* Returned status reflects latest known state.
* No state mutation occurs during query.
* Includes metadata such as timestamps and provider reference.

---

## US-006: Reconcile Payments

| Field          | Content                                      |
| -------------- | -------------------------------------------- |
| User Story ID  | US-006                                       |
| Role           | Finance Team                                 |
| Capability     | Match internal and external payment records  |
| Value          | Ensure financial correctness and consistency |
| Domain Concept | PaymentTransaction, PaymentProvider          |
| Business Rules | RULE-013, RULE-010                           |

### Acceptance Criteria

* External provider data can be ingested.
* Payments are matched against provider records.
* Discrepancies are identified and logged.
* Reconciliation results are auditable.
* Alerts are generated for mismatches.

---

## US-007: Prevent Duplicate Payment Processing

| Field          | Content                                                 |
| -------------- | ------------------------------------------------------- |
| User Story ID  | US-007                                                  |
| Role           | Payments System                                         |
| Capability     | Ensure idempotent payment creation and processing       |
| Value          | Prevent financial inconsistencies and duplicate charges |
| Domain Concept | Payment, IdempotencyKey                                 |
| Business Rules | RULE-005                                                |

### Acceptance Criteria

* Requests with the same idempotency key return the same payment.
* No duplicate transactions are created.
* System state remains consistent under retries.
* Duplicate requests are logged for observability.

---

# Summary

The Payments Domain user stories define the functional expectations of the system in a structured and traceable way. Each story connects:

* Business value
* System behavior
* Domain model concepts
* Business rules
* Acceptance criteria

Together, they ensure alignment between product intent and technical implementation.
